---
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Layout from "../../layout/layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Colors - Docs">
	<Header title="Colors"
		description="Loxt doesn't just make it easier to add your own custom themes, it even makes easier the use of colors in the terminal, all in one module!" />

	<main class="mt-5 gap-5 grid justify-center">
		<p>
			The colors module has terminal colors, bold, dim, underlined, inverted, hidden and more.
		</p>
		<p>
			Since the methods return strings you can chain them.
		</p>
		<pre class="bg-zinc-900 px-10 rounded-3xl">
			<code>
<span class="hljs-keyword">import</span> {`{`} <span class="hljs-title class_">Colors</span> {`}`} <span class="hljs-keyword">from</span> <span class="hljs-string">&#x27;loxt&#x27;</span>;

<span class="hljs-keyword">const</span> {`{`} underline, bold, red {`}`} = <span class="hljs-title class_">Colors</span>
<span class="hljs-variable language_">console</span>.<span class="hljs-title function_">log</span>(<span class="hljs-title function_">underline</span>(<span class="hljs-title function_">bold</span>(<span class="hljs-title function_">red</span>(<span class="hljs-string">&#x27;This is a text!&#x27;</span>))))
			</code>
		</pre>
	</main>
</Layout>